summary:
The Security Council,
Reaffirming its resolutions 1397 (2002) and 1402 (2002), 
Gravely concerned at the situation's deterioration and that 1402 (2002) has not been implemented,
1. Demands implementation of 1402 (2002) without delay;
2. Welcomes U.S. Secretary of State's mission and efforts by others, including special envoys and the UN Special Coordinator, for a comprehensive, just and lasting Middle East peace;
3. Requests the Secretary-General to monitor the situation and keep the Council informed;
4. Decides to remain seized of the matter.
